contract_type.raw_snippet:
Outsourcing Agreement
Between
Paratek Pharmaceuticals, Inc.
and
CARBOGEN AMCIS AG
Date
30 December 2016
Source: PARATEK PHARMACEUTICALS, INC., 10-K/A, 5/5/2017

WHEREAS:
A. Customer is the owner of certain technology and patent rights regarding the Product (as defined herein) having the description set out in Exhibit
A (Description of Product) and Exhibit B (Chemical Synthesis);
B. Customer has filed / intends to file for approval with the United States Food and Drug Administration and/or its foreign equivalents, an
Investigational New Drug Application (“IND”) and a New Drug Application (“NDA”), and/or the foreign equivalents thereof, for certain
formulations containing the Product;
C. Supplier is engaged in the business of performing contracted process development, Manufacturing and supply services of active pharmaceutical
ingredients (“APIs”) and intermediates; and
D. Customer desires that Supplier Manufacture the Product in bulk quantities, and Supplier desires to perform such services, each on the terms and
conditions set out in this Agreement.
contract_type.reasoning: The document is titled 'Outsourcing Agreement'. The 'WHEREAS' clauses further clarify that the Supplier will perform 'Manufacturing and supply services' for the Customer, where the Customer 'desires that Supplier Manufacture the Product in bulk quantities'. This clearly defines an outsourcing relationship for manufacturing and supply.

notice_period.raw_snippet: Customer delivers written notice of termination to Supplier at least [* * *] prior to the expiration date of the Initial Term, which termination shall be effective as of the expiration date of the Initial Term;
notice_period.reasoning: Article 2.1 states the agreement will 'automatically stay in force for a maximum of [* * *]' if a follow-on agreement is not reached, 'unless otherwise set forth in Section 18.1(a)'. Section 18.1(a) specifies that Customer can deliver written notice of termination 'at least [* * *] prior to the expiration date of the Initial Term' to make termination effective as of the Initial Term's expiration. This notice prevents the automatic 'stay in force'. The specific period is redacted.

renewal_term.reasoning: Article 2.1 describes the 'Renewal Term' as the agreement automatically staying in force for a maximum of a redacted period if a subsequent long-term agreement is not reached by a certain redacted date.
